Crockpot Peanut Chicken
This rich and creamy sauce is brightened with the flavors of lemon juice,
ginger root, and salsa in this fun chicken entree recipe.

INGREDIENTS:
8 boneless, skinless chicken thighs
1 cup chunky salsa
1/3 cup peanut butter
2 Tbsp. lemon juice
1 Tbsp. soy sauce
1 tsp. sugar
1/2 tsp. salt
1/8 tsp. pepper
2 tsp. finely chopped ginger root
1/2 cup chopped roasted peanuts

PREPARATION:
In 3 to 5 quart crockpot, mix all ingredients except chicken. Add chicken and
stir to coat. Cover crockpot and cook on LOW for 8-9 hours or until chicken is
thoroughly cooked and no longer pink in center.

Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and serve with hot cooked rice. 4 servings

Calories: 410
Fat: 25 grams
Sodium: 550 mg
Vitamin C: 10% DV
